TEAMS THAT PLAY TOGETHER, STAY TOGETHER
Dave & Buster’s offers both in person and virtual team building experiences. Whether it is ten coworkers or thousands of friends, we’ve got you covered.
Book Now
start control area
end div.is-control-area
THERE’S A REASON DAVE & BUSTER’S IS THE #1 COMPANY PARTY VENUE
CORPORATE TEAM BUILDING
Does your team have what it takes to WIN? Treat your group to an exciting afternoon of challenges that build skills such as strategy, leadership, teamwork and problem solving.
Contact a Planner
Dave's Epic Quest
Midway Showdown
Dave's Epic Quest
This team activity is a game-based “scavenger hunt”! Each team will be given a list of questions with varying point values based on the difficulty level to find the answer (all teams have the same list). Teams will either have to play games to find clues within the game, or search for clues in the Midway area. This team building experience is focused on teams having fun together and boosting team morale; however, strategy, great communication, leadership, division of strengths and time management are crucial if the teams hope to win!    INCLUDES:    100 CHIP POWER CARD ($20 VALUE)  D&B BRANDED TEAM ‘SWAG’  CERTIFICATE FOR 1st PLACE TEAM
Midway Showdown
The Midway Showdown is a head-to-head competition on arcade games! As players compete, their team should be behind them cheering them on. Every player on the team will rotate through every game. Points are awarded differently for each game. The team with the highest number of collective points wins! This teambuilder focuses on communication, teamwork & strategy.    INCLUDES:    100 CHIP POWER CARD ($20 VALUE)  D&B BRANDED TEAM ‘SWAG’  CERTIFICATE FOR 1st PLACE TEAM

Get To Know You

Join The Winning on All Cylinders Competition at Your Local D&B.
GET THE DETAILS.
JOIN THE CHALLENGE.
Join the Winning on All Cylinders Leaderboard Challenge at your nearest Dave and Buster's. Stack wins on any of the five participating games and see your name rise up the Leaderboard.
What is the Leaderboard?
The Leaderboard is a new, innovative experience that unlocks competitive game play, tracking wins in real-time and ranking top scores against guests locally and nationwide. A guests’ position on the Leaderboard will be indicated by their selected Play ID.
What is a Play ID? How do I get one?
A Play ID is unique identifier for guests at D&B that allows you to participate in Leaderboard challenges.  Play IDs can be obtained at a kiosk at your local D&B. In addition, you must be 13 years of age or older and join the D&B Rewards program to select a Play ID.
When does the Challenge take place?
This Leaderboard Challenge runs June 11th through September 1st.
How do I participate in the challenge?
You must be a member of the D&B Rewards program AND have a Play ID. Both can be obtained at your local D&B store at the kiosk. Follow the prompts to opt-in and head to any of the 5 games included in the challenge. If you secure a first-place win or jackpot, you’ve earned your spot on the Winning on All Cylinders Leaderboard.
How do I win prizes? Can I win more than once?
There are multiple ways to win in the Winning on All Cylinders Leaderboard Challenge. Every first place win or jackpot gets you a position on the Leaderboard AND an entry into the End of Summer Sweepstakes.
Every month, the Play ID with the top spot – 1st place – for each game at the store level will receive a prize. The local Leaderboards will be reset monthly.
At the end of the Leaderboard Challenge (Sept. 1) the 1st, 2nd, and 3rd place Play ID winners that have accumulated the most wins by game across all stores for the duration of the summer will receive prizes. The scoring is based on a cumulative total of wins/jackpots across June, July, and August.
National (end of summer) Sweepstakes Winner via random drawing. Guests can earn up to 2 entries per day; equaling a total of 25 entries across the summer program. Entry into sweepstakes can also be obtained through mail-in (no purchase required).
View All FAQs

What is the Leaderboard?
The Leaderboard is a new, innovative experience that unlocks competitive game play, tracking wins in real-time and ranking top scores against guests locally and nationwide. A guests’ position on the Leaderboard will be indicated by their selected Play ID.
What is a Play ID? How do I get one?
A Play ID is unique identifier for guests at D&B that allows you to participate in Leaderboard challenges.  Play IDs can be obtained at a kiosk at your local D&B. In addition, you must be 13 years of age or older and join the D&B Rewards program to select a Play ID.
When does the Challenge take place?
This Leaderboard Challenge runs June 11th through September 1st.
How do I participate in the challenge?
You must be a member of the D&B Rewards program AND have a Play ID. Both can be obtained at your local D&B store at the kiosk. Follow the prompts to opt-in and head to any of the 5 games included in the challenge. If you secure a first-place win or jackpot, you’ve earned your spot on the Winning on All Cylinders Leaderboard.
How do I win prizes? Can I win more than once?
There are multiple ways to win in the Winning on All Cylinders Leaderboard Challenge. Every first place win or jackpot gets you a position on the Leaderboard AND an entry into the End of Summer Sweepstakes.
Every month, the Play ID with the top spot – 1st place – for each game at the store level will receive a prize. The local Leaderboards will be reset monthly.
At the end of the Leaderboard Challenge (Sept. 1) the 1st, 2nd, and 3rd place Play ID winners that have accumulated the most wins by game across all stores for the duration of the summer will receive prizes. The scoring is based on a cumulative total of wins/jackpots across June, July, and August.
National (end of summer) Sweepstakes Winner via random drawing. Guests can earn up to 2 entries per day; equaling a total of 25 entries across the summer program. Entry into sweepstakes can also be obtained through mail-in (no purchase required).
